  "extra_note_en": "Vowel harmony is very important in Turkish. The geniş zaman suffix changes based on the last vowel of the verb stem. For most verbs it's predictable, but some common verbs are slightly irregular (e.g., gelmek → gelir, vermek → verir, bilmek → bilir, olmak → olur). Time expressions: her gün (every day), genellikle (usually), bazen (sometimes), her zaman (always), nadiren (rarely), Pazartesi günleri (on Mondays), sabahları (in the mornings), etc."
